# Clerk Authentication & Data Access Rules

All authentication is handled by [Clerk](https://clerk.com). The middleware in [middleware.ts](mdc:src/middleware.ts) uses `clerkMiddleware()` with `createRouteMatcher` so `/dashboard` and `/decks` redirect unauthenticated users to `/` (never to Clerk’s hosted sign-in page).

**This app has no dedicated sign-in or sign-up page.** The home page (`/`) contains the sign-in and sign-up modal buttons. When an unauthenticated user tries to access a protected page, always redirect them to `/`.

## Getting the Current User

In **Server Components** (protected pages), use `auth()` and redirect unauthenticated users to the home page:

```ts
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { redirect } from "next/navigation";

const { userId } = await auth();
if (!userId) redirect("/");
```

In **Server Actions**, use `auth()` and throw if not authenticated:

```ts
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

const { userId } = await auth();
if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");
```

In **API Route Handlers**, return a 401 response:

```ts
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

export async function GET() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) {
    return new Response("Unauthorized", { status: 401 });
  }
  // ...
}
```

## User-Scoped Data Access

Every database query **must** be scoped to the authenticated user. The `userId` from Clerk maps to the `userId` column in [schema.ts](mdc:src/db/schema.ts).

- **Reads**: Always filter by `userId` so users only see their own data.

```ts
const userDecks = await db.query.decks.findMany({
  where: eq(decks.userId, userId),
});
```

- **Writes**: Always set `userId` on insert.

```ts
await db.insert(decks).values({ userId, title: "My Deck" });
```

- **Updates / Deletes**: Always include a `userId` check in the `where` clause to prevent users from modifying other users' resources.

```ts
await db.update(decks).set({ title }).where(and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.userId, userId)));
await db.delete(decks).where(and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.userId, userId)));
```

- **Child resources** (e.g., `cards`): When accessing cards, verify ownership through the parent `deck` by joining or subquerying on `decks.userId`. Never trust a `deckId` from user input without confirming it belongs to the authenticated user.

## Rules

- Never expose data from one user to another. Every data-fetching or mutating operation must be gated on `userId`.
- Never trust client-supplied IDs alone — always pair them with a `userId` check in the query.
- Always call `auth()` and verify `userId` is non-null before any data operation.
- **No sign-in or sign-up pages.** Do not create dedicated `/sign-in` or `/sign-up` routes. All auth entry points use Clerk's modal mode from the home page.
- **Redirect to home.** When an unauthenticated user hits a protected server component page, use `redirect("/")` — never redirect to a `/sign-in` route.
- **Client-side auth UI:** Use modal `<SignInButton mode="modal">` / `<SignUpButton mode="modal">` with shadcn `<Button>` children, and `<UserButton />`. In Clerk v7 App Router, `SignedIn`/`SignedOut` are not exported from `@clerk/nextjs` for RSC — use `useAuth()` in a small client component (see [clerk-header-auth.tsx](mdc:src/components/clerk-header-auth.tsx)) or `<Show when="signed-in">` / `<Show when="signed-out">` in Server Components. Do **not** use `auth.protect()` or `redirectToSignIn()` in middleware; those send users away from `/` to a sign-in URL.
- Do not store passwords or implement custom auth flows — Clerk handles all of this.
